<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[264,1324,911,1457]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis box="[312,485,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygophore without process, height to length ratio 
<number box="[1106,1117,951,977]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[1122,1184,951,977]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.25">1.25</number>
. Subgenital plate triangular, with distal end acutely pointed, 
<number box="[857,894,991,1017]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as basal width, with three long stout setae arranged in an oblique row. Style with apophysis short, 
<number box="[1179,1231,1031,1057]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.33">0.33</number>
as long as total length, laterally curved, with bird­headlike apex. Connective with arms as long as stem; paraphyses strongly converging at basal 
<number box="[817,869,1111,1137]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.33">0.33</number>
then parallel, each paraphysis slightly twisted at apical 
<number box="[461,512,1151,1177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.33">0.33</number>
and then tapering to apex. Aedeagus compressed, with lateral ridges, dorsal apodeme well­developed, dorsal connectives well­developed, and stout, gonopore elongate on ventral margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
