<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[264,1324,911,1457]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis box="[312,414,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[429,573,1351,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decoratus">
<emphasis box="[429,573,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. decoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[724,852,1351,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colorata">
<emphasis box="[724,852,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. colorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rao and Ramakrishnan" authorityName="Rao and Ramakrishnan" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabourensis">
<emphasis box="[908,1076,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. sabourensis</emphasis>
Rao and Ramakrishnan
</taxonomicName>
as they all share an apically twisted apophysis. 
<taxonomicName box="[875,1021,1391,1416]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decoratus">
<emphasis box="[875,1021,1391,1416]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. decoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the two species in having a compressed aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
